OL,7,FThe local newspaper office was once a
OL,8,Ffixture on the British high street, as
OL,9,Ffamiliar and reassuring as the
OL,10,Fbutcher's, the baker's and the
OL,11,Fflorist's.
OL,13,FToday those outposts of
OL,14,Fcommunity-focused journalism have
OL,15,Fmostly disappeared, along with many
OL,16,Fbank branches and independent stores,
OL,17,Foften leaving behind a depressing mix
OL,18,Fof fried chicken takeaways, betting
OL,19,Fshops and charity outlets.
